      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the suggestion. You\u0027re right that the format-setup block (lines 75–84) is identical to doResize(), so I factored it out into a shared applyPixelFormat() helper that both call.\n\nI didn\u0027t substitute the whole doResize() call, though. The premise that there are zero connected clients here isn\u0027t quite accurate: initializePixelFormat() runs from the newClient hook, and libvncserver links the connecting client into screen-\u003eclientHead before invoking that hook (rfbNewTCPOrUDPClient() adds to clientHead, then calls newClientHook()). So doResize()\u0027s client iterator would actually visit the just-connecting client and set cd-\u003eskipFrame \u003d frameRate on it — delaying the very first frame — plus call setTranslateFunction() mid-handshake.\n\nExtracting just the shared format setup gives us the de-duplication you\u0027re after while keeping that client-iteration side effect out of the first-connect path. Updated the patch accordingly.",
