      "writtenOn": "2026-06-04T19:55:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good catch - this is actually worse than just a rejected client today. newClient() is a C callback invoked by libvncserver, and serverThread has no try/catch, so an elog thrown from probePixelFormat() propagates across the C frames and escapes the thread function -\u003e std::terminate() -\u003e the whole service dies. So one client connecting while the video device is unavailable currently takes down the daemon.\n\nFixed as you suggested: initializePixelFormat() is now wrapped in a try/catch in newClient(), returning RFB_CLIENT_REFUSE on failure. The cleanup falls out correctly - clientGoneHook is set before the throwing block, so on refuse libvncserver calls clientGone(), which decrements numClients back to 0 and frees the ClientData. formatInitialized stays false, so the next client retries the probe (good for transient device errors).\n\nI also fixed a related fd leak: the VIDIOC_G_FMT failure path in probePixelFormat() threw without closing the already-opened fd. Harmless when it crashed, but now that the service survives and clients keep retrying, it would leak an fd per failed attempt - so it closes the fd before the elog.",
      "parentUuid": "035c347c_1fcb06f4",
      "revId": "8b36b64e3b9d9c25e7f6ca1761dd0a58271c2463",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
